text: I built a prescreening tool for recruiters to be able to prescreen more candidates prior to doing their first interview.

So I wanted to build something that was very similar to a coding, kind of a prescreening coding test that software engineers would build, but something that you would send to non technical people, non software people like salespeople or marketing, and a lot of people who are interacting with other people all the time.
So this way you can get a measurement of some of their qualities outside of their resume.
So you don't end up hiring amazing salespeople on paper, but they're so toxic in the workplace that they bring everyone up, the rest of the performance of the rest of the team down.

I want us to build something that leverages AI to allow for the ease of make it easy to compare multiple people while also evaluating in a quantitative way some of the qualities that the company is looking for to hire from.
So these could be culture values.
So, for example, within the app itself, I have the culture values of my own company that I'm scoring against as an example and some other stuff, and that's what I've been building.
